  "body": "### Description\n*Type*: Bug\n\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\n*Summary*: when user does not set custom name, but he is added in your contacts, he is shown as `3-random-name::3-random name` in all chats. Quite often these names can be longer than 1 standard row on desktop app window. In this case, it can affect the location of timestamps or doesn't fit app size at all.\n\n#### Expected behavior\nusername is split into 2 rows \n\n#### Actual behavior\n<img width=\"344\" alt=\"username\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/48357763-9e003a80-e699-11e8-8129-91fc2907ab19.png\">\n\n\n### Reproduction\n\n- Open Status\n- Log in\n- Add user with long username to contacts (i.e. `0x0424a68f89ba5fcd5e0640c1e1f591d561fa4125ca4e2a43592bc4123eca10ce064e522c254bb83079ba404327f6eafc01ec90a1444331fe769d3f3a7f90b0dde1`)\n- check messages from this user in public chat, 1-1 chat or group chat\n\n### Additional Information\n* Status version: nightly 12/11/11\n* Operating System: Mac OSx",
